Consider the following immutable class:

 
{code:java}
public class C 
{
    public C(int x)
    { 
        X = x; 
    }    

    public static C Default { get; } = new C(0);
 
    public int X { get; }
}
{code}
 

The ImmutableTypeClassMapConvention refuses to map such a class, because when obtaining the properties of a type, it [calls the GetProperties|https://github.com/mongodb/mongo-csharp-driver/blob/v2.7.0/src/MongoDB.Bson/Serialization/Conventions/ImmutableTypeClassMapConvention.cs#L42] method with no parameters. According to the MSDN documentation, [both instance and static properties|https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/api/system.type.getproperties?view=netcore-2.1] of a type are returned in this case. 

The suggested fix is to consider instance properties only by setting the correct BindingFlags.

