The LINQ translator checks that all items in an array are serialized the same way by verifying that they are all serialized using the same serializer. But this approach doesn't account for polymorphism.

Given the following classes:
{code:java}
public sealed class C
{
    public int Id { get; set; }
    public Cat Cat { get; set; }
    public Dog Dog { get; set; }
}
 
public abstract class Animal
{
}
 
public sealed class Cat : Animal
{                               
}                               
                                
public sealed class Dog : Animal
{                               
}                               
{code}
The following query should work (but currently an exception is thrown):
{code:java}
var queryable = collection.AsQueryable()
    .Select(x => new Animal[] { x.Cat, x.Dog });
{code}

In case there is an expression that LINQ provider cannot translate because of not-yet-implemented expression Driver throws the following exception:

{code:java}
Expression not supported: "AROUT".Replace("OUT", c.CustomerId) because we were unable to determine which serializer to use for the result.
{code}

When 3.6.0 used to throw:

{code:java}
Expression not supported: "AROUT".Replace("OUT", c.CustomerId).
{code}

Currently we have number of places where SerializerFinder adopts approach similar to:

{code:java}
if (IsNotKnown(node) && IsKnown(leftExpression, out var leftSerializer))
{
    IBsonSerializer itemSerializer = leftSerializer.GetItemSerializer();
    AddNodeSerializer(node, itemSerializer);
}
{code}

The problem is in case if leftSerializer is IUnknowableSerializer, then IsKnown will return true and GetItemSerializer will throw an error, instead of deducing another IUnknowableSerializer.

h4. Summary

_When using either `EnumRepresentationConvention` or `ObjectSerializerAllowedTypesConvention`, if the type is recursive with a collection of the same type, initialization will fail with the following exception: "System.InvalidOperationException: ValueFactory attempted to access the Value property of this instance."_
h4. Please provide the version of the driver. If applicable, please provide the MongoDB server version and topology (standalone, replica set, or sharded cluster).

Applies to current codebase as of 2026-02-28 (tested by running unit tests) and C# driver version 3.6.0.
